The paper discusses algorithmic and game theoretic results for submodular welfare maximization problem, which is a well-studied problem in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper also mentions applications of this problem in social networks (cs.SI) and uses techniques from machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
